<br>
That aside, raising defense should not be much of a problem.<br>
First, get all the defensive buffs you can.  Get Virtue, Brells, Focus, PotG - whatever you can find.   Get KEI, too.<br>
<br>
1.  Find a place where you can pull a nice, borderline dark blue mob to a zone line, and are unlikely to get adds.  For example, pull a ravishing drolvarg to BW zone in Dreadlands.<br>
2.  Root the mob with a long root, Paralyzing Earth is best here.<br>
3.  Boon of Garou yourself.   +100 Dex will do wonders for skillup rate.<br>
4.  Cast Berserker Spirit on self.   <br>
<br>
Now, step into mob's melee range, and let it hit you till it breaks your Berserker.   As soon as you take damage, back off, recast Berserker, and step in range again.   You'll probably want to Cripple the mob - it won't make him slower, but it will lower its damage output a bit.<br>
<br>
Your Defense should go up fairly quickly.  <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
